ZH: 他磨磨蹭蹭地走到教室里。
EN: He walked into the classroom dawdlingly.

ZH: 别再磨磨蹭蹭了，否则我们会迟到的！
EN: Stop dawdling, or we will be late!

ZH: 她磨磨蹭蹭地收拾行李，总是迟到。
EN: She always packs her luggage slowly, always making her late.

ZH: 这个小男孩总是磨磨蹭蹭地吃饭。
EN: This little boy always eats his food slowly.

ZH: 我等了十分钟了，他还在磨磨蹭蹭地准备出门。
EN: I've been waiting for ten minutes, and he's still getting ready slowly.

ZH: 小狗磨磨蹭蹭地走到我的脚边。
EN: The puppy walked over to my feet slowly.

ZH: 她生病了，整天磨磨蹭蹭地动作很慢。
EN: She's sick, and she moves slowly all day.

ZH: 他们磨磨蹭蹭地准备了一个小时，才开始做作业。
EN: They took an hour to get ready before starting their homework.

ZH: 那个懒惰的人总是磨磨蹭蹭，什么事情都不愿意快点做。
EN: That lazy person always dawdles and doesn't want to do anything quickly.

ZH: 我讨厌别人磨磨蹭蹭，没有效率的行为。
EN: I dislike people who dawdle and behave without any efficiency.

ZH: 这个女孩对任何事情都磨磨蹭蹭，让人非常恼火。
EN: This girl dawdles with everything, which is very frustrating.

ZH: 他磨磨蹭蹭地拖延时间，结果错过了火车。
EN: He procrastinated and missed the train.

ZH: 别磨磨蹭蹭了，我们都等不及要开始聚会了。
EN: Stop dawdling, we can't wait to start the party.

ZH: 她总是磨磨蹭蹭地在镜子前面画妆。
EN: She always applies makeup slowly in front of the mirror.

ZH: 这类学生经常磨磨蹭蹭地完成作业。
EN: Students of this kind often slowly complete their homework.

ZH: 他磨磨蹭蹭地穿上衣服，已经迟到了。
EN: He's late because he puts on his clothes slowly.

ZH: 他们一直磨磨蹭蹭地谈论着这个话题，就是不做实际行动。
EN: They keep discussing this topic slowly but don't take any action.

ZH: 这个人总是磨磨蹭蹭地思考问题，浪费了很多时间。
EN: This person always thinks slowly and wastes a lot of time.

ZH: 我不喜欢跟他一起逛街，因为他磨磨蹭蹭，慢慢地走。
EN: I don't like shopping with him because he dawdles and walks slowly.

ZH: 每次开会他都会磨磨蹭蹭地迟到。
EN: He is always late for meetings, dawdling along the way.

ZH: 她磨磨蹭蹭地穿上鞋子，缓慢地离开房间。
EN: She puts on her shoes slowly and leaves the room leisurely.
